The body of the woman was found in a storeroom in her house on Tuesday after family members reported her missing. CAPE TOWN - Two men have been arrested in connection with the murder of a 51-year-old woman from Goodwood. The body of the woman was found in a storeroom in her house on Tuesday after family members reported her missing. Police say the woman’s Hyundai Elantra and a hard drive were missing from the scene. The police’s Frederick van Wyk says at around 11.20pm on Tuesday, the K9 Unit spotted the stolen vehicle and a VW Jetta driving in Elsies River. “Officers followed the suspicious vehicles until they both stopped. The two drivers, aged 30 and 32 years old, were arrested and a stolen hard drive was recovered. A post-mortem will be conducted to determine the course of death.” Both suspects will appear in the Goodwood Magistrate's Court soon on a charge of murder. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)